# SEO rules

## SEO priorities
- clear page titles
- useful meta descriptions
- strong headings
- crawlable content
- internal linking where natural
- performant pages

## Page content rules
- Use one clear H1 per page
- Make headings descriptive
- Write for humans first, then search engines
- Include relevant service/location wording naturally when appropriate
- Avoid keyword stuffing

## Technical rules
- Preserve existing metadata patterns unless improving them
- Do not create duplicate or conflicting metadata systems
- Do not hide important content inside inaccessible UI patterns
- Prefer plain, crawlable text for important service information

## Local/service relevance
When appropriate, help pages answer:
- what service is offered
- where it is offered
- who it is for
- how to get started

## Schema and metadata
Only add structured data when it is accurate and appropriate.
Do not invent business data.
Do not add fake FAQs.
Do not generate synthetic review schema.

## Performance awareness
SEO changes must not significantly harm performance.
Avoid heavy libraries or oversized media for minor SEO gains.